latestIgtvVideos.title: Banana 🍌 peanut 🥜 butter 🧈 cake 🍰
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Hi Everybody! 
Sundays are for Sundaes! 
Here’s an amazing banana, peanut butter cake recipe for you perfect cheat meal! 

Ingredients: 

1. 1/4 cup butter
2. One whole egg/ 1/4 cup curd ( preferably thick )
3. Two big ripe bananas (mashed)
4. 1 cup peanut butter ( I made mine at home and I used nutty peanut butter)
5. 3/4 cup Brown sugar
6. 1 tablespoon vanilla extract
7. 1 teaspoon baking powder
8. 1 cup oats flour
9. 1/2 cup all-purpose flour
10. 1/2 teaspoon salt
11. 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon powder
12. Chopped almonds 
13. Chopped dates

Method: 
1. Preheat your oven at one 80°C for about 15 to 20 minutes or put your sand on the store on low heat.
2. Beat the butter for a minute.
3. Add in your egg and beat that for a minute.
4. Add in your bananas, mix gently.
5. Add in your peanut butter. Again. mix gently.
6. Add in your brown sugar, mix.
7. Add in the vanilla essence, and aim your baking powder right into it
8. In a separate bowl mix all of your dry ingredients (oats flour, all-purpose flour, salt, cinnamon powder)
9. Add your dry mixture into your with wet mixture in parts and fold In gently.
10. Add your almonds and dates and fold in gently.
11. Pour your batter into your mould and bake it for 30-40 mins (180° C in an oven and low- medium heat on a stove) 
12. Once the room fills up with the aroma of your banana cake you know it’s most likely done. Poke a toothpick and if it comes out clean without crumbs sticking to it, it’s done.
13. Let it cool of and hour and then serve with ICECREAM 🍦

latestIgtvVideos.title: WORKING OUT ON YOUR PERIOD
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Today we’ll be talking about Exercising in your period. 

Exercise releases mood-boosting endorphins, which would take your mind off discomfort or pain.
The more active you are overall and more regular you are with your activity, the better your periods end up being less cramping, lighter flow

When your period starts, your estrogen and progesterone levels drop. And because of this, women can access carbohydrate/glycogen easily, this hormone shift makes fuel more accessible to your body, allowing you to push harder and get more out of High intensity workouts 

Even just a gentle stroll counts as exercise, and it may help you feel better to do some light and easy movement that helps reduce inflammation via blood flow.

I also feel, switching to period cups makes exercising easier and can avoid pad rash and uncomfortable dampness that comes with using pads 

All this said, if you're really just not feeling it, don't beat yourself up for it and take a day or two off.
